@goldsborough regarding the reason why I was relying on the installation stuff.
Initially it was just easier to have everything I needed there, then I thought the install layout would be more stable over time than the source tree.
+1 to avoid requiring the install for building. I'd keep make install for quickly gathering libraries and include files for shipping.

body:
@goldsborough regarding the reason why I was relying on the installation stuff.
Initially it was just easier to have everything I needed there, then I thought the install layout would be more stable over time than the source tree.
+1 to avoid requiring the install for building. I'd keep `make install` for quickly gathering libraries and include files for shipping.
